Nollywood actor, Jim Iyke has revealed why he refused to follow anyone one Instagram despite having over two million followers. According to the actor while speaking in an interview “Tea with Tay” podcast host Temisan Emmanuel, on Friday, Instagram is a market place for him where he only showcases his work and business. He said, “From day one I got on social media, I didn’t want to follow anybody. I wanted to establish the fact that this is a market place. It’s a pseudo reality there. It’s not what people want to take as their everyday life. Jim Iyke Finally Reveals How He Paid Uche Maduagwu To ‘Beat’ Him… Jim Iyke Arrested By Police At Lagos Airport For Slapping Dana… “If you see any of my posts, it’s tailored. I don’t post about my family. I don’t post my pleasures. There are certain things I think should be left for one to experience alone. “There are three tiers of life that I live. I live the private life, the public life, and the secret life. Social media is public life. If I want to make a statement in style, if I want to make a statement on my ideology and principles, if I want to market something, or if I want to set a new understanding on my opinion of something, that is where I should be. If I’m having a good time with people that don’t mind being on that platform, I go there. “I have kids that run the mall at every part of the world and no one will say, ‘I know that face’.”